The paper deals with polynomial inequalities and their applications in counting and optimization problems, which are topics that are commonly studied in computer science. The use of stable polynomials and their coefficients suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The study of monomials and sets of monomials in polynomials suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of approximation algorithms suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
